                <h1>Change Background Color in Adobe InDesign: Easy Steps</h1>
                <p>To change the background color in Adobe InDesign, select the "Rectangle Tool" from the toolbar and draw a rectangle covering the entire page. With the rectangle selected, go to the "Swatches" panel to choose your desired color. Send the rectangle to the back by right-clicking and choosing "Arrange" > "Send to Back".</p>
